Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of folding a piece of paper with creases in a specific way, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithms developed for recognizing simply foldable 1D crease patterns and deciding foldability of orthogonal crease patterns on rectangular paper suggest that the paper may also belong to sub-categories related to data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and scientific computing (cs.SC).
